				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Need Reply )<a name="17767"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 29 04 10:18 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If you have the cash, get the weapons with the instrument Mods.  Until you are 65 with over 100 AA, your melee damage isnt going to mean squat.  Haste is good for your bard to have though, cause our melee does do some DPS.  But Bards are much more useful in groups making thier songs more effective then adding a few more DPS.  A lot of times you wont BE meleeing, you will be tossing in charms, slows, mezzes, and other  stuff.  
<br />
You will se a lot more benefit from having instrument mods on your weapons.  Instrument swapping sucks, and it sucks hard and hungry, but it is worth it if it makes things run smoother.  With mods in instruments or gear you dont have to worry about swapping out instruments.  Saves you a lot of hassle. And the DPS on those instruments isnt bad at all.  h*ll, aug em up and you might use those till 65</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
