				<td colspan="2"><span>SBoZ is one of the most highly overrated weapons in the game IMHO. For a bard there are much better BARD ONLY weapons out there. Dizok wristsnapper should be all you need to carry you to 17 when you get dual weild, then invest in (a) gem-inlaid longsword (b) battle drummers main-gauche(sp?) or (c) a troubadour mace. Try to keep all your weapon skills up as you level, however, because receiving a rune stamped blade with only 1hblunt mastered REALLY sucks! For armor, acrylia plate can last you a long time, then the diety-specific cultural armors are a good investment. For starter gear till you are ready to get REAL stuff... i.e. stuff with a level requirement, I still like using the old quest armor like lambent, which you should be able to get a full set for 2-3k. That leaves alot of room for getting good weapons. In the beginning speed is better than dmg because of the dmg cap... I have seen lev 3 pallys using a 50 dmg 60 delay weapon, and the only thing i caan think is &quot;WHY!&quot; max hit with that thing has gotta be like 30 dmg anyhow. Oh well, this should get you up a bit until you can decide exactly your play style and gear requirements.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Impresario Amedaius Bladewhisper, 65 ladies' broken hearts and 170 aa meetings. <The Black Sheep of tunares flock she doesn't want to discuss>

